Reasoning: The paper deals with complexity classes and their collapses, which are central topics in computational complexity theory. Therefore, cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the structure of polynomial hierarchies, which falls under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science). The paper also mentions Buhrman and Fortnow's work, which relates to information theory and cryptography, falling under cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
